Salary: $3000 - $4500
Working Hours: Rotating shift
Responsibilities

  Plan, implement and monitor Ticket Service Provider’s overall supply chain, logistics and warehousing strategy and operations to maximize efficiency and productivity
  Develop and maintain good relationships with vendors and distributors in a Just–in– Time (JIT) environment in ensuring the best value for the organization through effective negotiation and partnership
  Collaborate with internal stakeholders within Ticket Service Provider in ensuring a healthy Supply Chain Management System is in place
  Determine, monitor and track key Supply Chain KPIs such as Stock Inventory, Lead Time, Shelf Life of Equipment, Components and Parts regularly
  Oversees daily operations and Identify process bottleneck, propose and implement solutions to resolve issues in a timely manner
  Develop work instruction for Supply Chain Management Team to support procurement, logistic and warehousing to support O&amp;M Team and Systems Engineering Team’s requirement
  Supports O&amp;M Team and Systems Engineering Team in developing short and long–term forecasts of Supply Chain and Financial Requirements to ensure Ticket Service Provider meets all necessary SLA objectives and are compliance to Regulators and relevant Service Partners
  Develop, plan and manage budget and resources are available for each Financial Year
  Plan, implement and manage procedures to optimize inventory control in warehouse
  Stay up to date with latest Supply Chain technologies and best practices ensuring continued implementation of asset management best practices for Ticket Service Provider to achieve ISO 55001 Asset Management Certification
  Perform any other duties as instructed by Management

Requirements:

  Degree in Supply Chain Management or Engineering with Financial Background is preferred
  1-3 years of relevant working experience in an O&amp;M industry involving Supply Chain Management, Procurement, Logistic or Warehousing
  Hands on experience on Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) Systems (eg. SAP, Maximo, Oracle)
  Able to work independently and in a team in a challenging environment

